headline: SWKS Q2 Deep Dive: Mobile Upside and Broad Markets Momentum Shape Outlook
summary: Wireless chips maker Skyworks Solutions (NASDAQ: SWKS) reported Q2 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 6.6% year on year to $965 million. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($1.02 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 13.9% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.33 per share was 7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
